  "texts": [
    "In the context of FedFM, we explore two main intellectual property protection strategies: 1) black-box fine-tuning, and 2) watermarking (Fig. 10).",
    "By integrating these intellectual property protection strategies, FedFM can ensure the secure Watermarking ServerBlack-Box Fine-Tuning and efficient use of FMs across distributed networks, making FedFM more robust and secure for collaborative AI model development Black-Box Fine-Tuning: Black-box fine-tuning refers to methods that fine-tune FMs without accessing the model's internal parameters [147].",
    "This approach is particularly relevant in FL, where maintaining the integrity and ownership of the original models is crucial.",
    "Black-box fine-tuning methods often add new parameters while keeping the original model unchanged, thus preserving the original model's intellectual property.",
    "For example, Fed-BBPT [148] is a prompt tuning framework that enables the joint training of a lightweight prompt generator across multiple clients."
  ]
}